#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Advice01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you're riding on a road, your horse \n"
"will just naturally follow the path, as is\n"
"its instinct.\n"
"Travel by road if you want to leave the\n"
"steering up to your steed and just enjoy\n"
"the scenery!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (red)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "Advice02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If a horse gets spooked or doesn't like \n"
"where it's at, it might shut down and\n"
"refuse to move at all.\n"
"If that happens, you can <2.se_co>target<3.re_co> while\n"
"mounted and then force the horse to\n"
"<4.se_co>move step by step<5.re_co>.\n"
"Just be sure you don't put your horse\n"
"in a dangerous situation."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Advice03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>To talk to someone while on horseback,\n"
"just <2.se_co>target<3.re_co> them first. \n"
"\n"
"But you won't be able to talk to anyone\n"
"if you're riding too fast, so slow it down."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Advice04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>If you get separated from your horse,\n"
"just whistle and it'll come running."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Advice05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Horses that have lots of <2.se_co>stamina<3.re_co> can\n"
"run at top speed for a long time.\n"
"\n"
"However, they can't turn well when\n"
"they're running at top speed.\n"
"\n"
"If your horse can't turn sharply, you're\n"
"more likely to hit obstacles, so think\n"
"before you ask your horse to sprint."
msgstr ""

