msgctxt "TalkHatu_01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Welcome to my <2.se_co>stable<3.re_co>.\n"
"We deal in all things horse related.\n"
"We also double as an inn.\n"
"<4.ra>Huh...<5.pa> I haven't seen your face before.<6.pa>\n"
"Do you know about the <7.se_co>stable<8.re_co> system?<9.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (short)
#. 6: raw
#. 7: choice
msgctxt "TalkHatu_02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Then allow me to explain.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"You can board your horse companions\n"
"with us<2.pa> and then summon them as\n"
"you please from our network of stables.\n"
"You may have come across <3.se_co>wild horses<4.re_co>\n"
"during your travels...\n"
"\n"
"If you catch one and ride it here to\n"
"register it,<5.pa> it will become your horse\n"
"companion.\n"
"One person can board up to five horses,\n"
"and you're able to swap horses in and\n"
"out as you please.\n"
"<6.ra>Do you...know how to catch a wild\n"
"horse?<7.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: sound
#. 4: sound
msgctxt "TalkHatu_03"
msgid ""
"<1.so>OK. To catch a wild horse, all you have to\n"
"do is approach it from behind—<2.pa>slowly, so\n"
"it doesn't notice you—and then hop on.\n"
"But these are wild animals we're talking\n"
"about, so if the horse you're riding starts\n"
"to act up, try soothing it.\n"
"It will eventually settle down, and when\n"
"that happens, bring it to me.\n"
"\n"
"<3.so>It may take a while for wild horses to get\n"
"used to being ridden.\n"
"\n"
"They may change directions or slow\n"
"down on their own until you earn their\n"
"trust and respect.\n"
"If your horse disobeys your direction,\n"
"you'll want to gently redirect it and\n"
"then calm it.\n"
"<4.so>And if you continue interacting that way,\n"
"your horse will naturally begin to trust\n"
"you and become more obedient."
msgstr ""

